-- England Beats New Zealand by 34 runs in One-Day Cricket Match
-- B y   T a r i q   P a n j a
-- 2013-06-05T20:48:10Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-06-05/england-beats-new-zealand-by-34-runs-in-one-day-cricket-match.html
England  beat New Zealand by 34 runs
in the third and final one-day cricket match between the teams
at Trent Bridge in Nottingham.  Ian Bell hit a top score of 82 and Jos Buttler smashed 47
runs in 16 balls as England scored 287-6 in its 50 overs. New
Zealand, which secured the series after winning the first two
games, lost regular wickets throughout its innings before being
bowled out for 253 with 21 balls remaining. Ross Taylor scored
71 for the tourists.  In two days England hosts the Champions Trophy, a one-day
tournament featuring eight nations. The tournament final takes
place on June 23.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Tariq Panja in London at 
